<|startoftext|>Question:I don't give a rat's - why not?
Answer:When I was little, I had my mom, when I was in college, my aunt, my cousin, my aunt's sisters. And I remember being pretty much always alone. I used to have a friend, and she was my aunt.  My mom was always with me but I wouldn't even let my cousin do anything with me.  I would take her in the park, walk all over the front yard of the park, even at church. All in all I didn't care...until the next day when I went to my cousin's funeral. It was a very lonely  day, I didn't notice her sitting there. When she brought the roses home to me, I felt a deep, warm feeling in my heart. I don't remember much after that, but from what I remember, she had the best heart of any girl anywhere.  But in my mind, I could see how her heart would really love me.  She was more than a daughter to me. I had always known how lucky I thought I was that I was so.  I mean, my aunt still remembers me even as one remembers her. So no, I don't give a rat's. And no, I don't give a rat's because nobody knows for sure what they're about to get out of me.  I just wish I did. ;)<|endoftext|>
